Anonymous Inner Class :
--------------------------------------

1. A class without any name.
2. Anonymous Inner class is generally used with abstract class and interface.

syntax:
ClassName referenceName = new ClassName(){
	// Override abstract methods
};

***************************************

Lambda Expressions:
1. Lambda Expression is a small block of code which is used to implement functional interface.
2. Marker Interface is an empty interface without any abstract methods.
3. Functional Interface is an interface with only 1 abstract method.

syntax:
InterfaceName referenceName = (arguments) -> {
	// override abstract method -> Only Implementation
};